Error: Common Error: "Minecraft Has Run Out Of Memory"

Solution: 1. Exit Minecraft completely.
2. Open the Minecraft launcher and click on "Launch options".
3. Click on the profile you are using, then look for "JVM Arguments".
4. Find the line that starts with "-Xmx".
   - This is the amount of RAM allocated to Minecraft.
5. Increase this number to allocate more RAM to Minecraft.
   - For example, if it is set to "-Xmx
